description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Medical Devices Department at Kettering General Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a vacancy for a highly motivated Medical Electronics Technician who will provide and support an integrated Medical Devices Service. The main duties will consist of carrying out reactive and planned maintenance on a wide range of medical devices. The individual will be responsible for the operational safety of these devices and will take a pro-active role in issues involving Health &amp; Safety and Risk Management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will liaise with the Trusts multi-disciplinary teams and Manufacturers to support when equipment is introduced into the Trust either by procuring or loaning for trial. Comprehensive records will be recorded and maintained on the Medical Device database in order to ensure compliance with appropriate legislation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The technician will provide technical advice, support and resources to support the activities of the Medical Equipment Library and of the Medical Device Trainer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be regular opportunities to train on individual device models&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Mary McDonald&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Medical Device Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address mary.mcdonald@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01536 493606&lt;/p&gt;
